Looking at this problem, I need to prove that the diagonal entries of a Wigner matrix have law ν.

The key insight is that:
1. `WignerMeasure μ ν n` is defined as `Measure.pi (wignerMeasureDist μ ν n)`
2. `wignerMeasureDist` assigns ν to diagonal entries (when `p.val.1 = p.val.2`)
3. The diagonal entry `(wignerMatrixMap n ω) i i` corresponds to the coordinate `⟨(i, i), le_refl i⟩` in `WignerSpace n`

```lean
/--The diagonal entries of a Wigner Matrix have law ν -/
lemma diagonalHasLaw (n : ℕ) (i : Fin n) :
    HasLaw (fun ω ↦ (wignerMatrixMap n ω) i i) ν (WignerMeasure μ ν n) := by
  rw [HasLaw]
  rw [WignerMeasure]
  have h_eq : (fun ω => wignerMatrixMap n ω i i) = (fun ω => ω ⟨(i, i), le_refl i⟩) := by
    ext ω
    simp [wignerMatrixMap, wignerMatrixMap', wignerMatrixEntryFunction]
  rw [h_eq]
  have h_dist : wignerMeasureDist μ ν n ⟨(i, i), le_refl i⟩ = ν := by
    simp [wignerMeasureDist]
  rw [← h_dist]
  exact Measure.map_eval_pi (wignerMeasureDist μ ν n) ⟨(i, i), le_refl i⟩
```
